info.headline: Wind Advisory issued December 28 at 6:35AM PST until December 29 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 7 AM PST THURSDAY ABOVE 1500 FEET... * WHAT...Southeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected above 1500 feet. * WHERE...Del Norte Interior, Southwestern Humboldt, Northern Humboldt Interior and Southern Humboldt Interior Counties. * WHEN...From 1 AM to 7 AM PST Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
